00:52.520 --> 00:56.434
Celeste was
born in America in 1986.

00:59.720 --> 01:02.360
Considering her parents'
background, education,

01:02.400 --> 01:04.596
and socioeconomic status,

01:04.640 --> 01:07.838
being somewhat on
the losing side of Reaganomics,

01:07.920 --> 01:12.472
the name of Latin origin seemed
an especially poetic choice.

01:12.520 --> 01:16.150
It carved her out some
predetermined destination,

01:16.200 --> 01:19.716
a route which to travel by.

01:19.760 --> 01:22.753
And many years before "Celeste"
rolled off the cultural tongue

01:22.800 --> 01:26.794
like a principled anecdote one
senses they were born knowing,

01:26.840 --> 01:29.674
she might not have been
described as all that special

01:29.720 --> 01:31.712
or conspicuously talented.

01:31.760 --> 01:34.878
However, she did possess
that proverbial "something,"

01:34.920 --> 01:37.879
which on occasion captured
the attention of her teachers

01:37.920 --> 01:40.310
and young peers.

01:40.360 --> 01:43.797
Despite what naysayers later
perceived of her ingenuity,

01:43.840 --> 01:47.197
she was actually
a very savvy businesswoman.

01:47.240 --> 01:50.995
In the beginning, she was kind
and full of grace,

01:51.040 --> 01:54.112
and at least she wrote
her own lyrics.

01:54.160 --> 01:56.994
No one could take that
away from her.

01:57.040 --> 02:00.192
She would be 13
going on 14 years old

02:00.240 --> 02:02.072
in the year 2000,

02:02.120 --> 02:04.715
the dawn
of the new millennium.

04:33.120 --> 04:35.237
Morning.

04:35.280 --> 04:38.512
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

04:38.560 --> 04:40.313
- Hello.
- Welcome back.

04:40.360 --> 04:43.432
- Good morning.
- Hi. Happy New Year.

04:43.480 --> 04:46.120
Therese, did you change
your hair?

04:46.160 --> 04:49.312
Uh, my sister cut it.
She's a hairdresser.

04:49.360 --> 04:52.114
Oh. Does she work in town?
I want a cut like that.

04:52.160 --> 04:54.595
Really? Uh, well,
she lives out of state.

04:54.640 --> 04:56.597
She was visiting us
for the holidays,

04:56.640 --> 04:58.791
but I can let you know
when she's back.

04:58.840 --> 05:01.639
Would you mind?
Sometimes you feel like a change.

05:01.680 --> 05:03.194
Sure, I can.

05:04.360 --> 05:05.760
- Hello.
- What's up?

05:05.800 --> 05:08.315
- Good morning.
- Hi.

05:08.360 --> 05:11.273
- Hi. Welcome back.
- Good morning.

05:13.640 --> 05:15.154
Okay.

05:16.440 --> 05:18.352
Welcome back, everybody.

05:18.400 --> 05:21.677
- Did you enjoy the break?
- Yes. Yeah.

05:21.720 --> 05:25.350
- Did you enjoy the break?
- Yes.

05:25.400 --> 05:28.438
Well, I received news
from Vice Principal Kane

05:28.480 --> 05:31.314
about our homeroom
computer appeal.

05:31.360 --> 05:33.079
What is it?

05:33.120 --> 05:35.589
I want to wait and share it
once everyone's arrived.

05:35.640 --> 05:38.678
We're waiting on, um,
Eric and Elyse.

05:38.720 --> 05:40.951
Well,
they're probably gonna take a while.

05:41.000 --> 05:43.799
Why is that?

05:43.840 --> 05:46.275
Aidan, let's not start
the year off at odds.

05:46.320 --> 05:49.677
Whatever you're saying to him,
you can save it for after class.

05:49.720 --> 05:52.599
He's here.
I saw Eric five minutes ago.

05:52.640 --> 05:54.816
- All right, then. We'll wait.
- Are we getting desktops?

05:54.840 --> 05:57.230
- I said we'll wait.
- Excuse me.

05:57.280 --> 05:58.839
Yes?

05:58.920 --> 06:01.594
My name is
Cullen Active.

06:01.640 --> 06:04.030
What?

06:06.400 --> 06:08.437
Yes, Cullen, I know.

06:17.520 --> 06:18.954
Celeste?

06:21.200 --> 06:24.113
Celeste, go stand in the back
with the others.

06:26.160 --> 06:27.992
Is she breathing?

06:28.040 --> 06:30.350
No.

06:30.400 --> 06:32.869
Celeste,
you need to get up

06:32.920 --> 06:35.310
and step away from the windows,
because in a few minutes

06:35.360 --> 06:37.397
there will be
an explosion.

06:37.440 --> 06:39.432
What are you doing?

06:39.480 --> 06:41.756
Why are you doing this?

06:43.480 --> 06:46.871
Stop! Stop!

06:46.920 --> 06:48.832
I'm standing.

06:48.880 --> 06:50.712
I'll stand.

06:53.520 --> 06:56.638
Now everyone,
please shut up and be quiet.

07:10.640 --> 07:12.916
Go back inside!

07:23.920 --> 07:25.639
Cullen?

07:27.520 --> 07:29.796
Cullen, please let us go.

07:35.520 --> 07:37.830
I killed plenty
of people already.

07:40.160 --> 07:42.959
I'm sorry.
I can't do that now.

07:43.000 --> 07:46.880
Please.
At least let everyone else go.

07:47.920 --> 07:49.912
I'll stay here with you.

07:51.280 --> 07:53.431
And what are
we gonna do?

07:59.400 --> 08:01.312
We'll pray together.

08:04.000 --> 08:06.674
Shh. Everything's gonna be...

08:46.760 --> 08:49.958
- Clear.
- Adam Seven, clear in the classroom.

08:54.760 --> 08:57.070
Clear!

09:10.840 --> 09:13.594
Adam Seven, be advised...
multiple 80s.

09:13.640 --> 09:15.996
Room 206, second floor.

12:36.480 --> 12:39.518
Breathe
in and hold your breath.

12:50.000 --> 12:51.673
Breathe.

12:53.840 --> 12:56.753
What are
you feeling now?

12:56.800 --> 12:59.076
I feel like
I'm on a boat.

12:59.120 --> 13:00.600
Nausea won't subside?

13:00.640 --> 13:02.438
It's not just that.

13:02.480 --> 13:04.711
I just feel
like I'm spinning.

13:04.760 --> 13:06.319
You think
it's in my head?

13:06.360 --> 13:08.272
No, I don't think
it's in your head at all.

13:08.320 --> 13:11.358
I just don't think it has anything
to do with your spinal injury.

13:11.400 --> 13:13.790
I need to sit.

13:13.840 --> 13:16.674
I'll get your chair.
Just a minute. Come on.

13:16.720 --> 13:19.394
Do you want to try
a few more steps?

13:19.440 --> 13:21.397
Okay. Good.

13:21.440 --> 13:23.159
All right.

13:25.960 --> 13:28.714
- There you go.
- Where's Dad and Eleanor?

13:28.760 --> 13:31.434
They went to
get us some food.

13:31.480 --> 13:33.551
Some of the other kids
have been complaining

13:33.600 --> 13:36.798
about their ears ringing
from the gun blasts.

13:36.840 --> 13:40.356
I talked to her doctor
about it, and...

13:40.400 --> 13:42.198
Great.

13:44.480 --> 13:47.359
- Hey, Mrs. Howard.
- Hello, Miss Celeste.

13:55.560 --> 13:58.997
I'm so sorry
I was sick.

13:59.040 --> 14:03.432
I should've
been there for you.

14:03.480 --> 14:06.917
I'm so grateful
you're alive.

14:06.960 --> 14:12.274
I think I would have died...
or just killed myself.

14:12.320 --> 14:14.960
I don't think
I could've standed it.

14:21.240 --> 14:25.234
I'm here now,
and I am never going to leave you.

14:25.280 --> 14:26.919
Ever.

14:30.000 --> 14:32.231
My God.

14:32.280 --> 14:35.398
Ellie,
I think I've done something terrible.

14:44.600 --> 14:47.479
What is it?

14:47.520 --> 14:50.433
It says here they found
Cullen's grandparents.

14:50.480 --> 14:52.776
They think that he shot both of
them three weeks before Christmas

14:52.800 --> 14:55.360
and lived with the bodies
over the holiday.

14:55.400 --> 14:56.550
- Ew!
- Dad...

14:56.600 --> 14:58.831
- Excuse me.
- Stop.

14:58.880 --> 15:02.556
I'm sorry. There are some news
people here requesting an interview.

15:02.600 --> 15:05.593
Oh, well, don't look at me.
It's up to her.

15:05.640 --> 15:08.951
I don't want anyone
to see me like this.

15:09.000 --> 15:10.753
You look fine.

15:12.080 --> 15:14.675
Can you talk
to them?

15:14.720 --> 15:16.154
Me?

15:16.200 --> 15:18.317
What am
I supposed to say?

15:18.360 --> 15:20.556
I wasn't there.

15:20.600 --> 15:23.877
Just tell them how sorry we
are for everyone that died.

15:26.160 --> 15:28.038
Call Mom.

15:29.200 --> 15:30.873
Are you sure?

15:36.000 --> 15:38.231
I can take you
to a telephone.

15:45.440 --> 15:47.193
Thanks, babe.

15:47.240 --> 15:50.438
- I think I want to try and sleep for a while.
- Good.

15:52.040 --> 15:53.872
I think I am going to try
and take your mother

15:53.920 --> 15:55.718
out to dinner
or something.

15:55.760 --> 15:57.877
Get her mind
off of things.

15:57.920 --> 16:00.640
Sure you don't need anything
else other than that keyboard?

16:00.680 --> 16:02.751
You know, I have a guitar
in the basement.

16:02.800 --> 16:05.076
Could bring that over,
teach you a little.

16:05.120 --> 16:06.713
Thanks, but...

16:06.760 --> 16:10.037
it's hard for me
to tilt my head down.

16:10.080 --> 16:11.673
So it starts like...

16:11.720 --> 16:14.713
so, one, two, three.

16:14.760 --> 16:16.638
Yeah.

16:16.680 --> 16:18.194
Twice.

16:56.040 --> 16:59.317
...remain
in critical condition.

16:59.360 --> 17:02.717
Hold them especially
in your prayers.

17:05.480 --> 17:07.517
Please join me now

17:07.560 --> 17:10.519
by turning to the page 13.

17:29.160 --> 17:31.391
I was informed earlier,

17:31.440 --> 17:33.432
and I guess some of you
are already aware,

17:33.480 --> 17:35.597
of last night's
arson attempt

17:35.640 --> 17:38.155
over at
the Active residence.

17:40.000 --> 17:43.152
Lieutenant Lynne at
the 120th Precinct has asked me

17:43.200 --> 17:46.034
to remind everyone
that that is the site

17:46.080 --> 17:49.118
of an ongoing
investigation,

17:51.600 --> 17:54.035
and its destruction would...

17:54.080 --> 17:58.836
gravely impair their officers'
ability to provide answers

17:58.880 --> 18:01.270
to the community's
many pressing questions.

18:02.520 --> 18:04.876
I would like to add...

18:04.920 --> 18:07.276
ferocious anger
prompted this,

18:07.320 --> 18:11.109
and we cannot have
any more anger

18:11.160 --> 18:14.676
or violence around us
this minute.

18:14.720 --> 18:17.792
I'll go a step further
by asking you all to please

18:17.840 --> 18:21.277
include the perpetrator

18:21.320 --> 18:24.836
of these vicious attacks
in your prayers.

18:27.200 --> 18:29.317
By this way of

18:29.360 --> 18:31.556
healing prayer

18:31.600 --> 18:34.320
and forgiveness,

18:34.360 --> 18:38.274
victims of this tragedy
will be...

18:38.320 --> 18:41.154
released from
their own grief

18:41.200 --> 18:45.114
and rage in the afterlife.

18:45.160 --> 18:48.517
Throughout the night, we'll be
asking New Brighton students

18:48.560 --> 18:51.234
to come up and share

18:51.280 --> 18:54.830
memories and recollections
with us.

18:56.920 --> 19:01.153
Please join me in welcoming
Celeste Montgomery

19:01.200 --> 19:03.954
from Stephanie Dwyer's
eighth-grade class.

19:22.320 --> 19:26.872
Um, I tried to prepare
something to say,

19:26.920 --> 19:31.517
but... I couldn't really put
my feelings into words exactly,

19:31.560 --> 19:34.951
so I thought
I'd do this instead.

19:35.000 --> 19:39.313
Uh, my sister, Ellie,
helped me a lot.

19:39.360 --> 19:41.431
This song is about us,

19:41.480 --> 19:44.075
and... it's for her.

