'cause I've been doing this a long time,

25:08.760 --> 25:10.680
and I can understand
if it's little overwhelming,

25:10.720 --> 25:13.110
but you have to trust
the process.

25:13.160 --> 25:15.914
The process works.
That's why you and your parents chose me

25:15.960 --> 25:18.031
to guide you
through this...

25:18.080 --> 25:20.720
strange and unpredictable
new process.

25:20.760 --> 25:24.231
So I want you to remember what I
told you at your parents' place

25:24.280 --> 25:26.920
the first time we met.

25:26.960 --> 25:30.397
You got to shut your eyes and
pretend like you're in your bedroom.

25:30.440 --> 25:32.896
You're just dancing in your bedroom,
and no one's looking at you,

25:32.920 --> 25:36.436
and you ain't got
a care in the world, okay?

25:36.480 --> 25:38.278
Okay.

25:38.320 --> 25:40.994
You got to tell me
if I'm not making any sense,

25:41.040 --> 25:44.256
'cause you got your head screwed on so
straight half the time I forget you're a kid.

25:44.280 --> 25:47.016
Don't worry yourself too much about the
technical stuff, 'cause I'm telling you,

25:47.040 --> 25:50.158
these people are not here to
listen to that fuckin' bass player

25:50.200 --> 25:53.398
riff like he's
Jaco Pastorius, hmm?

25:53.440 --> 25:55.671
- Okay.
- This is your show, okay?

25:55.720 --> 25:58.076
Remember that.
Run it. Okay?

25:58.120 --> 25:59.952
- You ready to get back into it?
- Yeah.

26:00.000 --> 26:02.276
- Good.
- But can you do me a favor?

26:02.320 --> 26:05.119
- Yeah.
- Can you watch your language around Ellie?

26:05.160 --> 26:07.516
It really bothers her
when people swear.

26:09.440 --> 26:11.591
Yeah, so I'm sorry.

26:11.640 --> 26:14.030
I-I, uh...

26:14.080 --> 26:17.198
I-I didn't realize
I was swearing at you.

26:17.240 --> 26:20.074
I wasn't thinking.
I'm sorry. Okay.

26:22.480 --> 26:24.176
So I just quickly
cut something together

26:24.200 --> 26:26.078
for the first
and the last verse,

26:26.120 --> 26:27.696
and it actually seems like
it's working really well.

26:27.720 --> 26:30.030
We might be over-thinking it.

26:30.080 --> 26:33.471
In the first verse, though, there's a
little crack or a hiccup or something

26:33.520 --> 26:36.160
in your delivery of
"'Cause I missed the train."

26:36.200 --> 26:38.669
So maybe we should just
take it from there?

26:38.720 --> 26:40.677
Great.
I'll nail that.

26:40.720 --> 26:42.916
Then we can get started
on "Body Talk."

26:42.960 --> 26:45.156
I'm sorry,
what section is that?

26:45.200 --> 26:47.840
It's the next track.

26:48.680 --> 26:50.239
Okay. Yeah.

26:50.280 --> 26:52.476
Let's get a head start
on tomorrow.

26:58.120 --> 27:00.430
Okay, here we go.

27:08.320 --> 27:10.676
I'm sorry I'm late.

27:10.720 --> 27:12.837
Thank you for waiting.

27:12.880 --> 27:15.759
Have you girls
been enjoying your stay?

27:15.800 --> 27:18.634
Yeah.
The hotel's very nice.

27:18.680 --> 27:20.592
Yeah. It's great.

27:22.160 --> 27:23.674
So, what's next?

27:23.720 --> 27:25.996
She beat me to the punch.

27:27.120 --> 27:29.316
Well, a few things.

27:29.360 --> 27:32.034
First, I've been meaning
to ask you if you, uh,

27:32.080 --> 27:34.356
have any background
in dance,

27:34.400 --> 27:36.232
or if your injury

27:36.280 --> 27:39.079
- prevents you from...
- I used to take ballet.

27:39.120 --> 27:40.315
And no.

27:40.360 --> 27:42.397
I just have to
be careful.

27:42.440 --> 27:44.272
That's great.

27:44.320 --> 27:46.835
Internally we've been discussing
a few upcoming events,

27:46.880 --> 27:49.554
performances we'd like
to pitch you for,

27:49.600 --> 27:52.115
and we'd love to set you up
with a choreographer.

27:52.160 --> 27:54.800
What kind of appearances?

27:54.840 --> 27:57.036
In-store performances,
things like that.

27:57.080 --> 27:58.958
It's a great way
to introduce

27:59.000 --> 28:01.151
your live experience
to the public

28:01.240 --> 28:05.678
and a great way for you to
get your feet wet in turn.

28:05.720 --> 28:08.280
Uh, Celeste,

28:08.320 --> 28:11.950
we really love
what you do here,

28:12.000 --> 28:14.674
but after everything
you've been through,

28:14.720 --> 28:18.077
I just think it's necessary to
be really straight with you

28:18.120 --> 28:20.555
and let you know
that there is

28:20.600 --> 28:22.557
no guarantee that
these new tracks will work.

28:22.600 --> 28:25.434
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
She's 14 years old.

28:25.480 --> 28:29.315
You don't need to talk that way to her.
Talk to me that way, not her.

28:29.360 --> 28:31.955
Let me finish, please.

28:34.920 --> 28:37.913
it would be unconscionable
for me to

28:37.960 --> 28:40.191
not make a young person
like yourself fully cognizant

28:40.280 --> 28:43.239
of the reality
of the situation.

28:43.280 --> 28:45.476
You've given us
a great demo,

28:45.520 --> 28:48.160
